        "client_msg_id": "96b1bfa9-aec4-4e04-bfd2-4fa373a470a8",
        "text": "Actually I remember now that <@U01ERR6MN9G> already mentioned this package on the rOpenSci Slack, where she says:\n\n&gt;  I clarify that:\n&gt; •  Automatic translations still don't have the quality we need for material that will be used for learning.  It can do more damage than good. \n&gt; • The message is, again, that people who don't speak English can have material of less quality than the people who speak English.\n&gt; • Translation is more than passing words from one language to another. It's not a good idea to have translations without a human review.\nHowever, the blog post does cover the idea of package maintainers using an LLM to get a first draft then editing as needed.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "g580131f5a7a",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/580131f5a7a4fa33c811dc6d20ab3ef8.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0004-72.png",
